docs.abstract: Parents who want their children to be great athletes sometimes uproot their lives to follow a dream. The costs are steep and the dedication is time consuming.
docs.snippet: Parents who want their children to be great athletes sometimes uproot their lives to follow a dream. The costs are steep and the dedication is time consuming.
docs.lead_paragraph: Members of the Hill family consider Jackson, Wyo., to be their home, but after spending parts of the past three years in Wellington, Fla., for the older Hill daughter’s equestrian training, they relocated there this year.

headline.main: Beyond Soccer Moms: Relocating for a Child’s Sport
headline.print_headline: Families Uproot Their Lives to Help Young Athletes Blossom

docs.abstract: India’s Paytm and global heavyweights like Google are moving aggressively to persuade reluctant Indians to give up their rupee notes.
docs.snippet: India’s Paytm and global heavyweights like Google are moving aggressively to persuade reluctant Indians to give up their rupee notes.
docs.lead_paragraph: ALIGARH, India — Signs and banners for Paytm, India’s biggest digital payments service, festoon Pooran Singh’s cellphone shop, where people drop in all day to add data or talk time to their prepaid phones.

headline.main: India Clings to Cash, Even as Tech Firms Push Digital Money

byline.original: By Vindu Goel and Suhasini Raj

docs.abstract: General Electric’s quarterly results showed how far the company has fallen, with big charges and sliding sales in its power generation business. G.E. also said the S.E.C. was examining its accounting.
docs.snippet: General Electric’s quarterly results showed how far the company has fallen, with big charges and sliding sales in its power generation business. G.E. also said the S.E.C. was examining its accounting.
docs.lead_paragraph: General Electric reported quarterly results on Wednesday that illustrated how far it has fallen, and the steep hill the company — once a titan of American industry — must climb to turn itself around.

headline.main: G.E. Reports $9.8 Billion Loss and Discloses S.E.C. Accounting Inquiry
headline.print_headline: G.E. Reports Huge Loss And Faces S.E.C. Inquiry

docs.abstract: Subscription revenue now accounts for 60 percent of the company’s total revenue, which increased 8 percent for the year, to $1.7 billion.

headline.print_headline: Subscriptions Top $1 Billion For Times Co.

docs.abstract: The Charleston Gazette-Mail has long had a reputation as a scrappy and tenacious local watchdog, but it isn’t immune to the pressures of the industry.
docs.snippet: The Charleston Gazette-Mail has long had a reputation as a scrappy and tenacious local watchdog, but it isn’t immune to the pressures of the industry.
docs.lead_paragraph: For decades, The Charleston Gazette-Mail in West Virginia has exposed corruption, greed and incompetence with a tenacity that was rewarded last year with journalism’s highest honor, a Pulitzer Prize. But the newspaper now faces a painful reality: No matter how strong its journalism, no publication is immune to the economic pressure on the industry.

headline.main: A West Virginia Newspaper Won Journalism’s Top Award. Now It’s Filed for Bankruptcy.
headline.print_headline: West Virginia Newspaper That Won a Pulitzer in ’17 Files for Bankruptcy

docs.abstract: Holywell, a town in Wales with dozens of local retailers, has struggled with the impacts of online shopping. It is applying technology to try and keep its shops open.
docs.snippet: Holywell, a town in Wales with dozens of local retailers, has struggled with the impacts of online shopping. It is applying technology to try and keep its shops open.
docs.lead_paragraph: HOLYWELL, Wales — Officials in this Welsh town will soon install free Wi-Fi along their lone shopping street. They are erecting the first electric car chargers in the area. And this past winter, small businesses began partnering with an American mobile payments system in the hope of getting more people in their stores.

headline.main: Tech Hit This Small Town Hard. Now, Locals Hope It Will Fuel a Revival.
headline.print_headline: A Town Hurt By Tech Turns To It to Rally

docs.abstract: G.E.’s unit that manufactures locomotives will be combined with the Wabtec Corporation, in the first move under John Flannery to shed an entire business.
docs.snippet: G.E.’s unit that manufactures locomotives will be combined with the Wabtec Corporation, in the first move under John Flannery to shed an entire business.
docs.lead_paragraph: John Flannery took a step on Monday toward his goal of making General Electric a “simpler, leaner” company by spinning off its railroad business in a deal valued at roughly $11 billion.

headline.print_headline: G.E. Spins Off Rail Unit in $11 Billion Deal as Part of Slimming Strategy
